HEADWORD: machilid
<hw>mach"i*lid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A wingless insect
living in dark moist places, as under tree trunks; they make erratic
leaps when disturbed; called also <altname>jumping
bristletail</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> jumping bristletail.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Machilidae</ent>⟦br⟧
